  <body id="d4">
   <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
    <head>
     Bureau R. F. + A. L. Office Sub Asst Comr <lb/>Sub Dist of Goldsboro
    </head>

    <opener>
     <dateline>
      <date value="1867-06-18">June 18, 1867</date>
      <name type="place">Goldsboro, NC</name>
     </dateline>
     <salute/>
    </opener>

    <p>Respectfully transmitted to the Sub Asst Com Sub Dist of Berne (<del hand="h1">__</del> HD
     Qrs. Asst Com Bureau State of North Carolina) Roderick Ham left the plantation of <hi rend="underline">Hay-ward
      Ham</hi> in the Spring of Summer of 1865 and went to New Berne N.C. <hi rend="underline">Sally Bess</hi> left
     the plantation of <hi rend="underline">Nicholas Bess</hi> about the same time and also went to New Berne. I
     infer that the parents name above and referred to in his letter as the <del hand="h1">_______
      ________</del>. and am informed, in direct, that they now reside as New Berne, N.C. </p>

    <closer>
     <salute/>
     <signed> C S Compton, Maj + Sub. Asst. Coms </signed>
    </closer>
   </div1>
  </body>
 </text>
